Hi Matt,

It's the same general idea, but subtract instead of add.

Each hour, B & T can do 1/6 of the job.  Each hour T alone can
do 1/10 of the job  That means that each hour B can do 1/6 - 1/10
= 4/60 = 1/15 of the job, so it'll take him 15 hours for the whole
thing.


